giving hamster attention does my hamster need a ton of attention i recently got back to soccer practice and it is hours a day and i also work a couple hours a day and when i get home i don't always feel like getting my hamster out how much does he need held and or petted a small amount of attention each day is better then none at all doing this about the same time is also a good thing i feel that if you do it a regular time combined with a bit of holding and some food it would be best maybe a special tidbit as a reward for being held and fresh food and water upon being returned to his cage is nice if you can keep that routine up at the same time each day and work in additional time when ever you can this should help keep your hamster tame and friendly and looking forward to your companionship be careful on over feeding treats too many could be a bad thing sometimes i sort out the large striped sunflower seeds from the mix and offer these as treats also whole grain cereal like cheerios are good keep it simple and healthy Hamster Bread Fancy rat Guinea pig Breastfeeding Cheerios Veganism Domestic rabbit Theory of conduct Spider Golden Hamster Dog training Japanese tea ceremony Cat Cereal Domestication Pet Pet skunk Organic farming Health insurance Rice Vegetarianism Omega-3 fatty acid Chicken Breakfast Animal testing Kosher foods Organic food Care Bears Falconry Social rule The Pet Sounds Sessions Urinary incontinence Agriculture Oat Food Current teachings of Prem Rawat Maize Sorghum XML Diarrhea Snake charming Folic acid Stomach cancer The Sims Monogamy Famine Livestock Genetic engineering Mealy Parrot Hemp Dog Scientology beliefs and practices Neopets Garfield Pet Sounds Internal ballistics Tocopherol Textile manufacturing Extreme Programming Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Zinc Zuiderzee Works Upholstery Sea-Monkey BitTorrent Customs and etiquette of Japan The Amazing Race House Mouse Sears Holdings Corporation Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints Green Day The Ashle